[
    {
        "content": "<p>Somewhere I've seen a paper on how to use string diagrams for vector calculus identities, but I'm not finding it - perhaps because the authors were not knowledgeable about the string diagram literature and didn't say \"string diagram\".</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/arula-ratnakar.bsky.social/post/3m2izzzovi22c\">Arula Ratnukar</a> is an impressive young neurobiologist who is studying Lagrangian mechanics just to improve her ability to write SF stories.  She had a test on vector calculus and did this nice calculation<a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/SKCnSgvWy6sLEjz5SaMV8jMF/vector_calculus.jpg\">.</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/SKCnSgvWy6sLEjz5SaMV8jMF/vector_calculus.jpg\" title=\".\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-original-dimensions=\"740x1000\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/21317/SKCnSgvWy6sLEjz5SaMV8jMF/vector_calculus.jpg/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p>This would be more pleasant with string diagrams - at least for people who understand string diagrams.</p>",
        "id": 543250486,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1759740099
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is not a paper, but maybe <a href=\"https://graphicallinearalgebra.net/\">graphicallinearalgebra.net</a>.</p>\n<p>edit: actually no, the website doesn't seem to mention vector calculus.</p>",
        "id": 543254865,
        "sender_full_name": "Peva Blanchard",
        "timestamp": 1759741273
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The Graphical Linear Algebra site works in the monoidal category with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>⊕</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\oplus</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">⊕</span></span></span></span> as the monoidal product, which is not at all what we want here. We want strings next to each other to represent the tensor product <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>⊗</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\otimes</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">⊗</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>I think the search we want to do is for 'vector calculus' along with 'Penrose graphical notation'. Indeed the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penrose_graphical_notation\">Wikipedia page for Penrose's notation</a> has a picture that essentially explains the whole thing:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/RHmo76oTnjxIwZ5XBb_GNRl6/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/RHmo76oTnjxIwZ5XBb_GNRl6/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"617x213\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/21317/RHmo76oTnjxIwZ5XBb_GNRl6/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 543256305,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1759741637
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's a paper which is probably the one you're thinking of: <a href=\"https://lowtonevoice.github.io/math-phys-tech/penrose-notation/english/main.pdf\">Vectors and tensors analysis by Penrose’s\ngraphical notation</a></p>",
        "id": 543256922,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1759741802
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>On the other hand, I kinda hate these stupid 'bubbles' representing the derivative. I think you should be able to do the whole thing without them. Write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C(\\mathbb{R}^3)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> for the real vector space of sufficiently nice functions on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}^3</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>. Then have one kind of string in your diagram for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{R}^3</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, and one for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C(\\mathbb{R}^3)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>. You can think of a vector field as an element of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⊗</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C(\\mathbb{R}^3)\\otimes\\mathbb{R}^3</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and represent it as a box in the string diagram with one of each kind of leg. Then the derivative is just a linear map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⊗</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C(\\mathbb{R}^3)\\to C(\\mathbb{R}^3)\\otimes\\mathbb{R}^3</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, and everything becomes normal string diagram manipulations with no bubbles.</p>",
        "id": 543258209,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1759742146
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's a first attempt at that:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/2w45FPkG9Y_1KlxM9oli1dlA/IMG_20251006_104225487_DOC3.jpg\">IMG_20251006_104225487_DOC3.jpg</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/2w45FPkG9Y_1KlxM9oli1dlA/IMG_20251006_104225487_DOC3.jpg\" title=\"IMG_20251006_104225487_DOC3.jpg\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-original-dimensions=\"1984x2952\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/21317/2w45FPkG9Y_1KlxM9oli1dlA/IMG_20251006_104225487_DOC3.jpg/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 543267358,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1759744662
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Another paper: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1911.00892\">Boosting Vector Differential Calculus with the Graphical Notation</a></p>",
        "id": 543293654,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1759752055
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, everyone!  That last paper, \"<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1911.00892\">Boosting Vector Differential Calculus with the Graphical Notation</a>\", is the one I was trying to remember!  In equation (28) it completes a string diagram proof of the identity Arula Ratkunar was proving,</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∇</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">A</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">A</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∇</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mtext> </mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext> </mtext><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∇</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">A</mi><mo>+</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\nabla(\\mathbf{A} \\cdot \\mathbf{B}) = (\\mathbf{A} \\cdot \\nabla)\\mathbf{B} \\,+\\,  (\\mathbf{B} \\cdot \\nabla)\\mathbf{A} + </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∇</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⋅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⋅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∇</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⋅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∇</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">A</span><span class=\"mord\">+</span></span></span></span> <br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">A</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">×</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∇</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mtext> </mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">×</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∇</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathbf{A} {\\times} (\\nabla {\\times} \\mathbf{B}) \\,+\\,  \\mathbf{B} {\\times} (\\nabla {\\times} \\mathbf{A}) </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">A</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">×</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">∇</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">×</span></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">B</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">×</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">∇</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">×</span></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 543310343,
